[2] Belgium: Meat processing plant outbreak
Date: Fri 7 Aug 2020
Source: Swiss info [edited]
https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/belgian-meat-processing-plant-confirms-67-covid-19-cases/45953848


A pork processing plant in Belgium reported 67 COVID-19 infections on Fri 7 Aug 2020, one manager of the firm told Reuters, joining a string of outbreaks at abattoirs and meat processing facilities around the world.

Westvlees tested and quarantined 197 workers from the meat cutting department of its plant in Westrozebeke, West Flanders, on Wed 5 Aug 2020 after some employees reported infections.

The company will test all 850 workers at the plant next week, as a precaution, product manager Manuel Goderis said on Fri 7 Aug 2020.

The meat cutting department is closed and will reopen on 17 Aug 2020 at the earliest. "For now, there is no reason to believe that there will be other cases," Goderis said.

Meat processing plants in Ireland and Greece have also reported clusters of new infections this month [August 2020], while countries including Germany, the United States and Australia have seen major outbreaks in the industry.

A German abattoir was shuttered in June 2020 after 1500 workers tested positive. More than 16 000 U.S. meatpacking workers had been infected by the end of May 2020, according to the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).

A CDC report in April 2020 said conditions in meat processing facilities could help spread the virus, including work on fast-moving production lines that hinder social distancing, and the physical demands of the work, which can make wearing face coverings difficult.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Meat processing plants have been identified as an industry with high risk of transmission, owing to the indoor nature of the work in relatively confined spaces with difficulties in adherence to social distancing. The above outbreak is just another example of the risks in industries providing food for consumption, along with seafood and vegetables/fruit packing facilities. - Mod.UBA]

